 TITLE

 	SunWindow

 VERSION

 	V1.16d

 AUTHOR

 	Bernhard Scholz

 	e-mail: scholz@informatik.tu-muenchen.de

 DESCRIPTION

 	SunWindow is a Workbench enhancment tool. In it's present
 	state it would be only useful for big PublicScreens.
 	SunWindow helps the user manageing all those nice little
 	window spread over the whole big working area. Therefore
 	SunWindow is some kind of the well know UNIX WindowManagers.
 	Following operations are currently available.

 		- automatic centering of new open windows so you
 		  never have to search for the window on the screen.
 		- recentering of the last active window after
 		  closing a window
 		- open a small mirror of the hole screen where you
 		  can perform window centering and window moving.
 		  This is the main purpose of the program.
 		- highly configurable.

